threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Synopsys ARCompact ARC700 cores, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This RISC-V ELF binary is classified as malicious, likely functioning as an IoT botnet or scanner. The most significant indicator is the presence of hardcoded UPnP/SSDP discovery strings ('M-SEARCH * HTTP/1.1' targeting 255.255.255.255:1900), which are commonly used by malware families like Mirai or Gafgyt to discover vulnerable network devices. Additional red flags include system-level reconnaissance paths (/proc/stat, /proc/cpuinfo) and a hardcoded Google Chrome User-Agent, typical for masking automated HTTP traffic.
